  <h2>This block is a Phase 1-stub for Unit 4</h2>
  <p class="sub">Full content lands when Unit 4 is built out.</p>
  <p>Block 3 models Earth's major carbon reservoirs — atmosphere, ocean, biosphere, geosphere — and the fluxes between them. Distinguishes <strong>fast</strong> pathways (photosynthesis / respiration on human timescales) from <strong>slow</strong> pathways (weathering / sedimentation on geological timescales). Why anthropogenic CO₂ is a problem: we're moving carbon from slow reservoirs (fossil fuels) to the fast atmospheric pool at a rate the slow cycle can't compensate for.</p>
